cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this work, please cite it as below."
title: "Memory Layers at Scale — Independent Reconstruction on Consumer Hardware"
abstract: >-
  An independent, from-scratch reconstruction of the Memory Layers at Scale
  architecture (Berges et al., 2024) integrated into Qwen2.5-7B-Instruct, trained
  on a single consumer GPU (AMD RX 7900 XTX, 24 GB, ROCm/WSL2). Includes the four
  build stages (naive memory layer, product-key, Memory+, frozen-backbone
  integration with warm-up), the empirically-found training recipe, and a detailed
  diagnostic of the lessons learned.
type: software
authors:
  - family-names: "Vouzellaud"
    given-names: "Alexandre"
license: Apache-2.0
keywords:
  - memory layers
  - product-key memory
  - language models
  - reproducibility
  - consumer hardware
  - ROCm
references:
  - type: article
    title: "Memory Layers at Scale"
    authors:
      - family-names: "Berges"
        given-names: "Vincent-Pierre"
    year: 2024
    notes: "arXiv:2412.09764 — architecture inspiration. This repository is an independent reconstruction, not a reuse of Meta's code."
